! Negative test: plain #bgl{} that mixes a declaration-shaped first line with
! subsequent bare statements must error.
!
! The autodetect peeks the first token(s): a `Type ident <terminator>` shape
! (here `attribute redtangent;`) routes the whole block to declaration mode.
! The following `x = 1;` is a bare assignment, which the global declaration
! parser rejects — proving the autodetect actually elevates and the mixed
! content is caught.
!
! Distinct from _test_inf_mode_bgldecl_rejects_stmt.inf, which exercises the
! same downstream error via explicit `#bglDecl{}`. This test covers the
! autodetect routing decision specifically.
!
! EXPECT_ERROR: Missing type before identifier 'x'

[ Main x;
    #bgl{
        attribute redtangent;
        x = 1;
    }
];
